 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# GLCM Cross Transformation\n",
    "\n",
    "An alternative to GLCM statistics within an image, is to take statistics across images.\n",
    "\n",
    "With similar requirements to Batched `GLCM`, images participating must be of the same shape.\n",
    "Combinations are between the Channel Dimension, while independent of the Batch Dimension.\n",
    "\n",
    "Remember that the expected Input Shape is: **B x H x W x C** or **H x W x C**"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.image import imread\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Read Image"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1f5774f9af0>"
     },

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ar = imread(\"../../../data/image.jpg\")[:250, :250]\n",
    "plt.imshow(ar)"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Theory of Cross GLCM\n",
    "\n",
    "We find all pair combinations in the channel dimension.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here, we see that `ar` has 3 channels.\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus the combinations are\n",
    "- [Channel 0, Channel 1]\n",
    "- [Channel 0, Channel 2]\n",
    "- [Channel 1, Channel 2]\n",
    "\n",
    "### Combination Order\n",
    "\n",
    "To inspect the combination order, you can find them using `itertools.combinations`"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "(250, 250, 3)"
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ar.shape"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "[(0, 1), (0, 2), (1, 2)]"
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from itertools import combinations\n",
    "list(combinations(range(ar.shape[-1]), 2))"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GLCM Progress:  94%|█████████▎| 170k/182k [00:00<00:00, 330k Cells/s] "
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(246, 246, 3, 7)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from glcm_cupy import GLCMCross\n",
    "\n",
    "radius = 2\n",
    "gc = GLCMCross(bin_from=256, bin_to=16, radius=radius)\n",
    "ar_gc = gc.run(ar)\n",
    "print(ar_gc.shape)"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "As above:\n",
    "- `ar_gc[:,:,0,:]` corresponds to the cross between Channel 0 and 1.\n",
    "- `ar_gc[:,:,1,:]` between Channel 0 and 2.\n",
    "- `ar_gc[:,:,2,:]` between Channel 1 and 2."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Plot Transformations\n",
    "\n",
    "Note how we find the pair indices via `itertools.combinations`\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "Text(0.5, 0.98, 'GLCM Cross Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 1080x1440 with 42 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot in a grid\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 20))\n",
    "grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,\n",
    "                 nrows_ncols=(7, 3),\n",
    "                 axes_pad=0.4)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax_ix = 0\n",
    "for f_ix, title in zip(range(ar_gc.shape[-1]),\n",
    "                           (\"HOMOGENEITY\", \"CONTRAST\", \"ASM\", \"MEAN\",\n",
    "                            \"VARIANCE\", \"CORRELATION\", \"DISSIMILARITY\"), ):\n",
    "    for e_ch_combo, ch_combo in enumerate(combinations(range(ar.shape[-1]), 2)):\n",
    "        ax = grid[ax_ix]\n",
    "        ax.imshow(ar_gc[..., e_ch_combo, f_ix] ** (1 / 3))\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f\"{title}, {ch_combo}\")\n",
    "        ax_ix += 1\n",
    "fig.suptitle('GLCM Cross Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "\n",
    "- `glcm-cupy` works with batched images, for convenience and a small speed up!"
